t: "So when you meet the disbelievers Ë¹in battleËº, strike Ë¹theirËº necks until you have thoroughly subdued them, then bind them firmly. Later Ë¹free them either asËº an act of grace or by ransom until the war comes to an end. So will it be. Had God willed, He Ë¹HimselfËº could have inflicted punishment on them. But He does Ë¹this only toËº test some of you by means of others. And those who are martyred in the cause of God, He will never render their deeds void"